caption: I’ve been here several times but brought my parents when they last visited and they loved it! We had dinner at the bar and for a fairly picky group, the menu had something for everyone. The vibe is definitely funky, but in the best way possible. The sushi and grilled skewers are creative and rich on flavor. The winner though, which seems odd for a Japanese izakaya is the cheeseburger! The mix of the ground meats coupled with the bun makes for an awesome combination. The cocktails are fun too, they even make special drinks for you of the bartenders are not too busy!

Definitely one of the best of places to dine in, in the Fenway area.  The service is great, so is the food.  We tried the charred broccoli, the two vegan sushi options they had and few other other dishes. Although the number of items for vegans are limited, they are made to perfection and leave a lasting impression. They also have some great drinks so yes this place is amazing! In other words, great place... Don't miss it!

Really bad experience as an uber eats driver, I had a pickup order for a customer. I went in the restaurant to pickup, the girl at bartender said 15 minutes wait. I went back to my car in freezing cold that was parked 3 min walk away... came back after 20 minutes, order was not ready. She requested me to give her 15 more minutes, told me to go back to car, came second time the order wasn’t ready... it had been over an hour, I waited for that order and ended up canceling it because the girl at bartender kept lying about the wait time. Please understand that if the order is going to take time, the driver should be made aware about it so that they can move onto next order. I made $0 that whole hour, I have family to feed as well. I didn’t mind waiting for 15-20 minutes but over an hour was just ridiculous. Its a humble request that please let the drivers know the “real approximate” wait time so they can go ahead and move onto next order, please and thank you.

Hojoko is a great place with a very diverse menu. The name itself is a tribute to the old Howard Johnson that used to be there. The decor inside is awesome and has many old school music and art on the walls. Some of the drinks come in crazy containers. The cheeseburgers and fries are tremendous. The sushi is also great. The wasabi roulette is a fun thing to do with a group. They basically put a big piece of wasabi hidden in one of the pieces of a hamachi roll and give a pina colada-like drink in a baby bottle to the person who gets the wasabi. The truffle shiitake tempura is really good with some truffle froth in top.

I met up with a coworker last night for drinks and snacks at Hojoko (previously the Howard Johnson's from way back) to see what it was like. We got there around 5:30 and sat at the bar, as we were the first ones there. The bartender was very knowledgeable, friendly and poured a very good (albeit $13 small) cocktail (shout out to Jen!). Well the food was very delicious I was a bit disappointed by the cost/amount ratio. We started off with an order of fries and the chicken win from the Robata Grill. The fries are shoestring style and very hot & tasty. The wings while hot and delicious were lacking in numbers; only 3 wings for $9 - yikes. Then, we ordered chicken tails (there's such a thing) skewer for $6, Kurobuta pork belly skewer for $6 and the sashimi salmon for $9. Both of the skewers were tasty and easy to eat, but didn't have a lot. Then, the sashimi salmon was excellent, but only came with 4 thin slices. So, we had a nice time, but I left still hungry and wondering how it all came to just under $85. I guess that's what you get when you mix trendy and the new Fenway neighborhood.

Great atmosphere, vinyl records playing all sorts of good music, cool environment and great staff. The food! Just one example of many: Mushroom yakisoba, probably the best vegetarian dish I have ever tasted, I am not much of a vegetarian aficinado so it might be that I am just new to veg dishes. Cabbage bites, long slim “perfect bite” noodles and tiny mushrooms gently covered with a thin tasteful layer of smooth juices, sliding easily through my lips and at the bite of my teeth gives just the right resistance before they burst and release a descrete taste of garlic, cinnamon and freshly cut grass  (powdered fresh aonori). To complete the experience of these aromatic flavours and solid textures - in comes the fermented daiko with its sligthly sour, salty and spicy palette, which together with the perfect umami taste completes the dish. I could be wrong, but I think this is the sexiest dish I have ever had. Thank you Hojoko for the great recommendations, service, atmosphere and food mastery performed by your team.

Pricey, but amazing food.
There is anime playing in the back of the restaurant on a projector. I got the calf brains, they were spicy and had dehydrated onions on top, which were moving from being rehydrated.

Came for dinner, not drinks. Fun atmosphere for sure, but food is very very overpriced for the portion sizes. Paid $17-18 for a "decent" bowl of ramen the size of a small cereal bowl. Would recommend for a fun night out but definitely not for any type of substantial meal.
Good drinks and beer on tap, highly underrated spot.
instruments available to play in lobby and drinks are great!

The food is absolutely amazing but even more so is the staff. Jennifer was my waitress and she was so attentive and friendly. She cares a lot about the customer and the food she presented to us. Nicole also served us and she was so funny and caring. The atmosphere is truly remarkable but if you eat here please ask for her. Jenn is one of the best waitresses I've had at any restaurant!!!
Okay and kind of expensive. No reason to go unless you are staying at the hotel. Even so they wouldn't allow me to have a drink because all I had was a New York state ID.... I'm in my 30s
Amazing! The burger was easily the best burger I've had in my life. The staff is knowledgeable about the menu and very helpful.
Great cause it was opened late, like wicked late. But the food was mediocre... Very small menu also. I don't know if it was cause we went late or if that was the full menu
Fun night out awesome drinks
More vegetarian options would be great!
Excellent, the food is just great and the prices more than reasonnable.
Come here if you're looking for something a little different around fenway!
They are pretty generous with their good Japanese whiskeys.

Anyone complaining about the price needs to realize where they are and the type of restaurant they are in. I decided to try brains for the first time here. Absolutely delicious. I always say don't knock it till you try it. I also had their salmon sushi. The rolls fell apart slightly but tasted good. After my meal I realized why they charge $12 for a drink. I left with a wonderful buzz and no mad cow disease from the boiled brains. I say that's worth a rant and a rave. Would recommend to anyone who'd like to try something new.
Great cocktails, dj, and crowd.  Try the nyc to Tokyo cocktail

Food was delicious, but if you're a picky eater like me you probably won't find anything to eat. One of the best california rolls I have had in boston. They have an allergy info sheet you can can request too. I came here for the cocktails. Plates are small/for sharing which can get expensive.

Honestly I was pleasantly surprised by the quality of the food considering most fusion restaurants butcher both cultures that it's trying to "fuse". My only gripe is that the food isn't really worth the price! A couple of shrimp and rice cakes for $14? Don't expect to get full very quickly. Would recommend the okonomiyaki though! It's surprisingly well done.
Glorious food, great service and funky decor. What's not to like about that. 😀
Always have a blast here, plus the food being on point is always a plus! 👍👍
Food is killer. Very accomodating although not many vegetarian options. Music and entertainment is always well recieved. Hojoko is lit fam.

Just grabbed a few drinks here. Super cool idea and atmosphere. Hipster spot all the way. We enjoyed all the different areas to hang out. Although there was some type of incense or something burning the whole time that was a little too strong. Other than that a really cool place to grab a drink or bite to eat.
Comfortable place. Food was delicious with enough variety on the menu to please any appetite. Service was quick and courteous.
(Translated by Google) The place is very nice, excellent care and cleanliness 👌  (Original) El lugar es muy agradable, excelente atención y limpieza 👌
Great selection of Japanese bar foods done well.  A killer sake list as well.  Fun vibe!
Good food, great drinks.

Excellent food. Come early if you have kids because it gets packed and lively after 6:30. The brains on crack is off the hook. Sashimi bowl and Tuna Poke hands down amazing. Would pass on the potstickers. California roll was one of the best I've ever had. Can't wait to come again. Drinks are strong.

Super cool atmosphere with great food and drink selection. Small plates are definitely small though so I would recommend ordering 3 things per person. The sashimi bowl was very tasty as were the calves brains and shrimp sushi roll. The service was also great, attentive and friendly. I would recommend this for dinner and drinks.

Fun, lively atmosphere with an open kitchen and awesome drinks. Really impressed with their allergen awareness- my husband has shellfish and mushroom allergies, which can be challenging with Japanese food, but the servers made sure everything we ordered was safe and warned us about any possible cross-contamination. Attentive and friendly service all around.
Definitely overpriced
